    </div>
    <div class="section-body">
      <div class="corrige">
        <div class="corrige-header" onclick="toggleCorrige(this)">▶ Corrigé Exercice 2</div>
        <div class="corrige-body">
          <div class="corrige-step"><div class="cs-num">a)</div><div class="cs-text">u₁ = (9+2)/6 = 11/6 ≈ 1.833. u₂ = ((11/6)²+2)/(2·11/6) = (121/36+72/36)/(22/6) = (193/36)·(6/22) = 193/132 ≈ 1.4621.</div></div>
          <div class="corrige-step"><div class="cs-num">b)</div><div class="cs-text">HR : uₙ ≥ √2. Montrons uₙ₊₁ ≥ √2. uₙ₊₁ − √2 = (uₙ²+2)/(2uₙ) − √2 = (uₙ² + 2 − 2√2 uₙ)/(2uₙ) = (uₙ − √2)²/(2uₙ). Or (uₙ−√2)² ≥ 0 et uₙ > 0, donc uₙ₊₁ − √2 ≥ 0. ✓ Initialisation : u₀ = 3 ≥ √2 ✓.</div></div>
          <div class="corrige-step"><div class="cs-num">c)</div><div class="cs-text">uₙ₊₁ − uₙ = (uₙ²+2)/(2uₙ) − uₙ = (uₙ²+2−2uₙ²)/(2uₙ) = (2−uₙ²)/(2uₙ). Or uₙ ≥ √2, donc uₙ² ≥ 2, donc 2−uₙ² ≤ 0, donc uₙ₊₁ ≤ uₙ : décroissante. ✓</div></div>
          <div class="corrige-step"><div class="cs-num">d)</div><div class="cs-text">Décroissante et minorée par √2 : converge. Point fixe : ℓ = (ℓ²+2)/(2ℓ) → 2ℓ² = ℓ²+2 → ℓ² = 2 → ℓ = √2.</div></div>
          <div class="result">✓ lim uₙ = √2  (suite de Newton-Raphson pour √2 !)</div>
        </div>
